claim: The War of 1812 took place in part on the Maritime Provinces of Nova Scotia, New Brunswick, Prince Edward Island, and Cape Breton which make up Atlantic Canada and this region served as on of the theaters of the war.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Atlantic Canada is the region of Canada comprising the four provinces located on the Atlantic coast , excluding Quebec : the three Maritime provinces -- New Brunswick , Prince Edward Island , and Nova Scotia -- and the easternmost province of Newfoundland and Labrador .
